FuncDef:
The static-user interface-list command configures an access interface list for static users.
The undo static-user interface-list command deletes an access interface list of static users.
By default, no access interface list is configured for static users.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the name of an interface list.
The value is a string of 1 to 32 case-insensitive characters.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To allow multiple IPv4 static users on the same network segment to go online through multiple specified interfaces, run the static-user interface-list command to configure an access interface list. Then, run the interface command to bind a specified interface to the configured interface list.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
